3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses regularity conditions for probability density functions, which can be related to data structures and algorithms for processing probability distributions. 
4. cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper may involve mathematical software for computing and analyzing entropy rates and related quantities. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper may have applications in modeling and analyzing stationary processes in social and information networks.
